programme.title: A Shoe Addicts Christmas
programme.desc: Department store employee Noelle visits Christmases of past, present and future as her guardian angel helps her navigate her wishes for a connection with her father, her dream career and love.

programme.title: Santa Tell Me
programme.desc: A design show host finds a letter from Santa promising to meet her true love, a man named Nick, by Christmas Eve. Meeting three Nicks complicates her search.

programme.title: Boyfriends of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Marketing executive Lauren must learn to open her heart with the help of four ghosts of ex-boyfriends who visit her leading up to Christmas.

programme.title: A Dream of Christmas
programme.desc: An ambitious married woman gets more than she bargained for when her wish to be single again is granted. She awakens to discover shes got everything shes ever wanted, except her husband. She resolves to find him a second time.

programme.title: Mistletoe Match
programme.desc: When Olivia goes under cover to report on the popular annual Mistletoe Match event, she meets Thomas, who is just as skeptical about the event as she is. Sparks fly, but she may risk losing a promotion for the romance she never saw coming.

programme.title: The Christmas Retreat
programme.desc: When Kims boyfriend breaks up with her instead of proposing, Kims mom takes her away to a Christmas retreat to reconnect with the spirit of the holiday. When she gets there, she meets newly unemployed Mark.

programme.title: Holiday Date
programme.desc: Brooke is dumped right before Christmas and enlists the help of actor Joel to play the role of her boyfriend for the holidays.

programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: Hollywood on Set

programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: Christmas in Evergreen: Letters to Santa
programme.desc: Lisas trip home to Evergreen for the holidays finds her shepherding an effort to save the towns beloved general store, fulfilling the wishes of a Christmas past and finding a romance full of Christmas magic.

programme.title: Christmas in Evergreen: Tidings of Joy
programme.desc: A skeptical writer shows up in Evergreen to get the scoop on the towns famed passion for Christmas during a search for a long-lost time capsule.

programme.title: Christmas in Evergreen: Bells Are Ringing
programme.desc: As Michelles wedding approaches, Hannah steps up to finish the new Evergreen museums launch while questioning her future with Elliot.

programme.title: Arthur Christmas
programme.desc: Santas youngest son (James McAvoy) sets out on an urgent mission to deliver a present to a forgotten child before Christmas morning dawns.

programme.title: A Season for Family
programme.desc: Maddys adopted son, Wesley, has just one wish for Christmas -- to meet his brother, Cody, who was adopted into a different family. Circumstances soon bring the two siblings together while sparks fly between their respective parents.

programme.title: Mystery on Mistletoe Lane
programme.desc: New to town, Heidi Wicks and her kids discover a Christmas mystery in their historic home. Local handyman and historian David helps along the way, finding his own surprising connection.

programme.title: Holiday Touchdown: A Chiefs Love Story
programme.desc: Chiefs superfan Alana tries to win the Fan of the Year Award as a Christmas gift for her family, falling in love with someone in the Chiefs front office along the way.

programme.title: Christmas Getaway
programme.desc: After a surprising breakup with her boyfriend, a travel writer decides to go on the picturesque Christmas vacation planned for the two of them, alone.

programme.title: Christmas at the Plaza
programme.desc: When historian Jessica is hired to create the Plazas Christmas display, she finds more than facts while teaming up with handsome decorator Nick to bring the display to life.

programme.title: A Biltmore Christmas
programme.desc: A magical hourglass sends modern-day screenwriter Lucy Hardgrove to the set of the 1947 holiday movie classic "His Merry Wife!" However, before she can return to the present, Lucy must make things right or threaten to alter the future forever.

programme.title: The Christmas Train
programme.desc: A cynical journalist must get from Washington, D.C., to Los Angeles in time for Christmas, and his only option is to take the train.

programme.title: Sister Swap: A Hometown Holiday
programme.desc: Two sisters find a new sense of purpose and discover what they both truly need in life during the holidays.

programme.title: Sister Swap: Christmas in the City
programme.desc: Two sisters find a new sense of purpose and discover what they both truly need in life during the holidays.

programme.title: A Timeless Christmas
programme.desc: A man travels from 1903 to 2020, where he meets a tour guide at his historic mansion and gets to experience a 21st century Christmas.

programme.sub-title: La Gran Muralla; LEGO Batman: la pelcula; Huye!

programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: The Sweetest Christmas
programme.desc: A struggling pastry chef is thrilled to learn that she has made it to the finals of the American Gingerbread Competition, but distractions in her love life threaten to derail her dreams of taking home the grand prize.

programme.title: A Perfect Christmas
programme.desc: Newlyweds Steve and Cynthia have a few secrets to keep as their families arrive for the holidays: hes just been laid off, and shes pregnant.

programme.title: Three Wise Men and a Baby
programme.desc: Three brothers get the surprise of their lives when they are forced to work together and care for a baby over the holidays.
